      • setFolder

        public VMTypes.ClonePlacementSpec.Builder setFolder(java.lang.String folder)
        Virtual machine folder into which the cloned virtual machine should be placed. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0. If property is null, the system will use the virtual machine folder of the source virtual machine. If this results in a conflict due to other placement parameters, the virtual machine clone operation will fail.
        Parameters:
        folder - New value for the property. When clients pass a value of this class as a parameter, the property must be an identifier for the resource type: Folder. When methods return a value of this class as a return value, the property will be an identifier for the resource type: Folder.

If property is null, the system will use the resource pool of the source virtual machine.       • setHost

        public VMTypes.ClonePlacementSpec.Builder setHost(java.lang.String host)
        Host onto which the cloned virtual machine should be placed.

        If getHost() and getResourcePool() are both specified, getResourcePool() must belong to getHost().

        If getHost() and getCluster() are both specified, getHost() must be a member of getCluster().

        . This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0. If this property is unset, if getResourcePool() is unset, the cloned virtual machine will use the host of the source virtual machine. if getResourcePool() is set, and the target is a standalone host, the host is used. if getResourcePool() is set, and the target is a DRS cluster, a host will be picked by DRS. if getResourcePool() is set, and the target is a cluster without DRS, InvalidArgument will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        host - New value for the property. When clients pass a value of this class as a parameter, the property must be an identifier for the resource type: HostSystem. When methods return a value of this class as a return value, the property will be an identifier for the resource type: HostSystem.

      • setCluster

        public VMTypes.ClonePlacementSpec.Builder setCluster(java.lang.String cluster)
        Cluster into which the cloned virtual machine should be placed.

        If getCluster() and getResourcePool() are both specified, getResourcePool() must belong to getCluster().

        If getCluster() and getHost() are both specified, getHost() must be a member of getCluster().

        . This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0. If getResourcePool() or getHost() is specified, it is recommended that this property be null.
        Parameters:
        cluster - New value for the property. When clients pass a value of this class as a parameter, the property must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource. When methods return a value of this class as a return value, the property will be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.

      • setDatastore

        public VMTypes.ClonePlacementSpec.Builder setDatastore(java.lang.String datastore)
        Datastore on which the cloned virtual machine's configuration state should be stored. This datastore will also be used for any virtual disks that are created as part of the virtual machine clone operation unless individually overridden. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0. If property is null, the system will use the datastore of the source virtual machine.
        Parameters:
        datastore - New value for the property. When clients pass a value of this class as a parameter, the property must be an identifier for the resource type: Datastore. When methods return a value of this class as a return value, the property will be an identifier for the resource type: Datastore.
